1
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:22,133
Your mother's death anniversary
is near.

2
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,333
Do you already have plans?

3
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:24,367
None.

4
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:27,167
I know that Celeste
is quite material

5
00:00:27,233 --> 00:00:29,500
but I wonder if she is also
a mother material.

6
00:00:29,567 --> 00:00:31,833
What is good about Celeste...

7
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:34,533
is that she knows how to love
someone without being pushy.

8
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:35,833
That's why I know that Celeste

9
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:38,700
is going to be a good second
mother to Tiffany.

10
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:41,467
I know that you want us
to patch things up

11
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:44,233
because it's been a long time
ago.

12
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:48,933
How do I possibly forgive
the man that I loved first

13
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,033
but also the first
one to hurt me?

14
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:52,200
Where is Father?

15
00:00:52,267 --> 00:00:53,600
He left early.

16
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:55,633
He will go somewhere important.

17
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,700
Who else he will go to?

18
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:00,733
Maybe we can patch things up
soon.

19
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,467
Well, I think that day is today.

20
00:01:02,533 --> 00:01:03,500
I hope so.

21
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,800
Hi, Mother.

22
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:10,600
Love is also like sewing.

23
00:01:10,667 --> 00:01:16,100
You should give all your heart,
mind, and soul

24
00:01:16,167 --> 00:01:19,033
when you love,

25
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:24,633
but you will also get hurt
but don't be scared.

26
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,267
Don't be discouraged

27
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:31,367
because even if you get hurt,
stumble,

28
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:33,433
or go astray in the end,

29
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:37,300
you can still learn a lesson
for you to become a good person.

30
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:42,100
You know, Mother...

31
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:45,600
you will be glad.

32
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:48,900
I've decided to reconcile
with father.

33
00:01:50,267 --> 00:01:52,433
You will be the witness.

34
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:56,100
There's nothing that time
can't heal.

35
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:59,233
You should leave the anger
in the past.

36
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:04,600
Until the heart remembers
what it had long forgotten,

37
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:06,533
that is to love again.

38
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,067
Nothing...

39
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:18,433
maybe he has no plans
of coming, Mother.

40
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,500
I can't contact him.

41
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:25,633
It's my fault,
I expected too much.

42
00:02:33,633 --> 00:02:35,800
Love, how are you feeling?

43
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:38,200
Don't worry.

44
00:02:38,267 --> 00:02:39,467
I'm okay.

45
00:02:39,533 --> 00:02:44,000
Didn't the doctor say that
my sugar level is normal?

46
00:02:44,067 --> 00:02:45,367
That's good.

47
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:47,900
Celeste?

48
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,333
Did you eat already?

49
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,133
That's good. I'll cook.

50
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:58,067
Celeste, we dropped
by Matnog (town) to buy this.

51
00:02:59,133 --> 00:03:00,800
Here, it's big!

52
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:03,467
Father, that's a lot!

53
00:03:03,533 --> 00:03:07,533
Yes! Your mother said,
I should buy them all

54
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:12,467
so your Manay (Sister) Celeste
can eat crab in coconut milk!

55
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:14,367
Manay, that's a winner!

56
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:17,200
I'm sure you will like
my mother's specialty.

57
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:23,867
That's your important
appointment?

58
00:03:23,967 --> 00:03:25,167
That?

59
00:03:26,167 --> 00:03:27,333
Celeste, no.

60
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,533
Your Auntie Adora and I came
from the hospital.

61
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,000
I had her checked
by the doctor.

62
00:03:31,067 --> 00:03:34,900
She often feels dizzy
and had a stomach ache.

63
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:39,067
Father, Mother,
why didn't you tell me?

64
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,700
I should've come with you.

65
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:45,967
Your father insisted that
I should have a check-up.

66
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:47,567
I'm okay.

67
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,567
It's better to be sure.

68
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:51,267
So, you prioritized her...

69
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:56,267
instead of visiting my mother?

70
00:03:56,367 --> 00:03:57,700
It's her again.

71
00:04:30,067 --> 00:04:31,567
Celeste?

72
00:04:31,633 --> 00:04:32,900
That's the truth, right?

73
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,500
She is always your priority

74
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:38,900
even when mother
was still alive.

75
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:41,033
Celeste, I'm sorry.

76
00:04:41,967 --> 00:04:44,000
It's really an emergency.

77
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:45,733
I didn't forget that today

78
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:48,900
is your mother Lucinda's
death anniversary.

79
00:04:48,967 --> 00:04:51,733
Your Auntie Adora and I
have plans

80
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:54,033
that the four of us
including Sebastian

81
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:55,600
will visit your Mother Lucinda

82
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:56,800
That's fine.

83
00:04:56,867 --> 00:04:58,733
It's okay, it's done.

84
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:02,233
I went to her this morning...

85
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:05,167
because I will never allow
my mother

86
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:08,167
to be an afterthought the way
that you do.

87
00:05:10,033 --> 00:05:13,167
You just allow Manay to answer
you back that way.

88
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:14,233
What's her issue?

89
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:17,067
I don't understand either.

90
00:05:18,167 --> 00:05:20,433
Sometimes I also get tired.

91
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,700
What?

92
00:05:22,933 --> 00:05:23,833
Come again?

93
00:05:25,667 --> 00:05:29,533
You are getting tired?

94
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,333
Oh my God.

95
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:32,733
It's me who is tired!

96
00:05:35,133 --> 00:05:38,200
I have had enough of this crap!

97
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:44,033
You know, maybe it's time
that you all know...

98
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:48,567
how insensitive you all are!

99
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:52,533
I...

100
00:05:54,767 --> 00:05:57,533
I've been hurting for almost
half of my life

101
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:00,433
because of all of you!

102
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,567
Celeste...

103
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,600
You're so clueless,
aren't you?

104
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:09,067
Honestly, I never remember
a single day,

105
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:11,100
an important day in my life
that you were there.

106
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:17,833
Birthday, Christmas,
New Year, graduation.

107
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:21,833
Did I say anything?

108
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:24,067
Did I make a fuss about it?

109
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:25,533
You didn't hear anything
from me.

110
00:06:27,767 --> 00:06:30,000
I was only asking
for one day...

111
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:33,233
one day.

112
00:06:35,233 --> 00:06:37,533
You know how important
this day to me is.

113
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,767
I was only asking for one
day and you can't give it.

114
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:46,233
Father, you can't give
one day...

115
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:47,967
for me...

116
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:49,300
for your daughter.

117
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:53,633
For your wife who died
because of all of you!

118
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:56,300
Manay, you're getting out
of hand!

119
00:06:56,367 --> 00:06:57,633
No, you shut up.

120
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:01,567
Have you ever seen your mother
cry herself to sleep?

121
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:07,067
Have you ever seen her
lose her mind

122
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:10,300
because the man of her dreams
left her

123
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:11,967
and took her heart away?

124
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:18,000
Have you ever seen your mother
waiting under the rain...

125
00:07:18,067 --> 00:07:19,233
because he never came back
for her

126
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:20,933
because he chooses his mistress?

127
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,733
Do you think I'm happy?

128
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,967
Do you think I'm happy
with all of these?

129
00:07:39,033 --> 00:07:40,033
No, I'm not!

130
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:41,833
I'm empty...

131
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,600
I'm empty.

132
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:47,267
I'm broken...

133
00:07:48,067 --> 00:07:49,733
because I don't have a mother.

134
00:07:52,433 --> 00:07:54,700
So, don't tell me that
I'm getting out of hand...

135
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,333
because you don't know
how it feels.

136
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:02,900
Yes, Manay, Father has a lot
of shortcomings

137
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:04,867
but you're also guilty, right?

138
00:08:04,933 --> 00:08:06,800
You don't even use his last
name.

139
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:10,500
Do you think that's okay
with father?

140
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,267
Sebastian, that's enough!

141
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,167
Father, no!

142
00:08:15,233 --> 00:08:18,500
She needs to know
that she has a bad attitude!

143
00:08:18,567 --> 00:08:19,500
I said that's enough!

144
00:08:22,867 --> 00:08:23,733
Celeste...

145
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:32,067
I'm doing everything to pay
for all my sins against you

146
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:33,900
and your mother Lucinda.

147
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:36,933
I'm not asking for anything.

148
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:42,133
What I want earlier was
to be with you...

149
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,867
even just a day.

150
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:46,433
You know, if you think
about it...

151
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,233
if only you came...

152
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,600
I've waited there for so long.

153
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:54,767
If you had come...

154
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,567
I would've forgiven you.

155
00:08:58,633 --> 00:08:59,867
I'd be okay by now...

156
00:09:02,533 --> 00:09:04,433
but you choose them.

157
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:08,433
Celeste, I'm really sorry.

158
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:13,000
What I've said to you earlier
is true.

159
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,267
I didn't forget that today

160
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:18,400
is your mother Lucinda's death
anniversary.

161
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,600
The truth is, last week,

162
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:26,100
I ordered for the remains
of your mother Lucinda

163
00:09:26,167 --> 00:09:27,767
to be transferred
to a much better gravesite.

164
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:32,367
I want to surprise you
Celeste on this day.

165
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:37,933
I want the four of us
to visit her together.

166
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,833
Let's visit your mother Lucinda.

167
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,133
It was really an emergency.

168
00:09:46,833 --> 00:09:50,767
I thought that your Auntie Adora

169
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:53,200
might have a hyperglycemia
attack.

170
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:56,233
The doctor said the situation
will get worse

171
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:57,767
if this is ignored.

172
00:09:58,533 --> 00:10:00,167
It's dangerous...

173
00:10:00,233 --> 00:10:04,267
so I was forced to take
your Auntie Adora to the doctor.

174
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:08,733
And besides Celeste,
the day is not yet over.

175
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:14,067
We can still visit
your Mother Lucinda now!

176
00:10:14,133 --> 00:10:15,633
The four of us will go there
together!

177
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,700
- Let's leave right now.
 - It's too late.

178
00:10:16,767 --> 00:10:18,367
- Let's go now.
- It's too late.

179
00:10:18,433 --> 00:10:20,700
It's okay now. It's fine.

180
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,200
Never mind.

181
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:28,567
You know, honestly, thank you
because of what I saw today.

182
00:10:28,633 --> 00:10:30,333
You did me a favor.

183
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,133
You only proved that

184
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,667
I can't depend on you anymore.

185
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:42,533
So, if you expect me to glorify
your father's name,

186
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:49,367
he's all yours.

187
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,467
Huh...

188
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,667
Patricio...

189
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:21,633
let's leave Celeste alone.

190
00:12:23,567 --> 00:12:28,400
Maybe she will also realize that
she went overboard.

191
00:12:30,033 --> 00:12:31,200
Love...

192
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,933
you should understand
my daughter.

193
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:41,667
That's what I'm doing...

194
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:43,167
that's what we're doing.

195
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:49,500
Until now...

196
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:52,033
Celeste sees me
as a mistress...

197
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,233
even if we're married,

198
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:58,500
even if I'm already your wife.

199
00:13:00,567 --> 00:13:03,033
Yes, we were wrong
when we hurt Lucinda...

200
00:13:06,300 --> 00:13:08,267
but when I loved you
I didn't know

201
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,533
that you already have a family.

202
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:30,467
When I catch a lot of fish,

203
00:13:30,533 --> 00:13:32,133
when we harvest a lot of pili...

204
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:39,933
the three of us will take
a stroll at a mall in Manila!

205
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:43,367
No need, Love.

206
00:13:43,433 --> 00:13:46,633
Celeste and I are already happy
here in Sorsogon,

207
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:47,900
right, Celeste?

208
00:13:47,967 --> 00:13:49,400
Yes, Mother.

209
00:13:49,467 --> 00:13:53,600
What's important is the three
of us are together.

210
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:57,633
Mother, Father, I love you.

211
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,700
- I love you too, Celeste.
- I love you too, Celeste.

212
00:14:00,767 --> 00:14:02,133
Thank you.

213
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:57,933
When you followed me in Naga
to fight for your love

214
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,367
I stayed away from you,
remember?

215
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:03,467
Even when I'm already one month
pregnant with Sebastian.

216
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,867
I didn't take you away
from Lucinda.

217
00:15:09,767 --> 00:15:11,667
I didn't want to destroy
your family.

218
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:14,767
I'm not a bad person,
Patricio...

219
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:19,500
but that's how Celeste sees me.

220
00:15:24,033 --> 00:15:27,200
That's what the people believed.

221
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,367
I'm so tired...

222
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:37,367
of Celeste's wrong accusation
against me,

223
00:15:37,467 --> 00:15:42,233
as well as my relatives,
as well as my friends!

224
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,700
As well as the people
who don't know very well.

225
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:56,867
When I chose to love
and marry you,

226
00:15:56,933 --> 00:15:59,667
when I chose for us to raise
a family,

227
00:16:00,633 --> 00:16:02,400
Lucinda is already gone.

228
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,167
But for the people...

229
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,633
I'm still wrong.

230
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,367
For Celeste...

231
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:14,433
I'm a worthless person.

232
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:21,667
But I will endure...

233
00:16:23,267 --> 00:16:24,700
I'll be patient.

234
00:16:27,033 --> 00:16:28,333
But Patricio...

235
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:35,767
how long will I fight
my decision to love you?

236
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:43,500
Someday everything
will be all right.

237
00:16:46,967 --> 00:16:50,367
Someday...

238
00:16:54,933 --> 00:16:57,233
Do you want to look for Celeste?

239
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:58,400
Let's go.

240
00:17:01,133 --> 00:17:02,467
Come on...

241
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,400
Come on, you should buy that.

242
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:18,100
That's only fifty pesos.

243
00:17:18,167 --> 00:17:19,700
That's just fifty pesos.

244
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:22,533
Maybe you also want this,
so it's one hundred fifty pesos.

245
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:26,767
Miss, have you seen my daughter
Celeste?

246
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:27,700
How about you, Sir?

247
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:28,900
No.

248
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:30,767
She didn't come here.

249
00:17:32,067 --> 00:17:33,033
Is that so?

250
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:33,967
Yes.

251
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:35,767
- Thank you.
- Okay.

252
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:36,933
Come on, that's fifty pesos.

253
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,000
Credit is not allowed.

254
00:17:38,067 --> 00:17:41,133
Come on, buy it all.

255
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:45,067
I'm sorry the subscriber
could not be reached.

256
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:46,433
Please try your call again
later.

257
00:17:48,933 --> 00:17:51,033
Buy these all now.

258
00:18:32,733 --> 00:18:34,067
It's beautiful here, Mother.

259
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:37,833
You know when your father
and I were just lovers,

260
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:39,667
we often come here.

261
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:45,667
Look at that.

262
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:52,733
Whenever you are sad
just look at the sea.

263
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:59,933
Even if I'm gone,
it's like you are still with me.

264
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:09,900
Why did you do that to me?

265
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:11,733
I gave you everything, didn't I?

266
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:17,433
What does she have
that I don't have?

267
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:21,667
Is she more beautiful?

268
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:25,467
Is she a better cook?

269
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,900
Is she more caring to you?

270
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:33,667
Patricio,
whatever my mistake is,

271
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:34,733
whatever my shortcomings,

272
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,933
I'll correct them...

273
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,433
just leave that woman!

274
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:47,267
Lucinda, I can't leave
Adora anymore.

275
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:50,600
She is pregnant.

276
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:54,933
Love...

277
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:57,667
Love...

278
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,467
how about our daughter?

279
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:02,800
How about Celeste?

280
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:06,100
You love me, right?

281
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:08,700
You love me, Patricio.

282
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:15,433
Celeste...

283
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,033
How about Celeste?

284
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:28,633
Mother, come on, let's eat.

285
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:35,100
Mother...

286
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,667
you haven't eaten
since this morning.

287
00:20:39,933 --> 00:20:41,300
Let's eat.

288
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:47,100
Mother, you will get sick.

289
00:20:48,533 --> 00:20:50,100
Come on, Mother.

290
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:20,100
Mother...

291
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:22,833
don't wait for father anymore.

292
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:27,300
He will never come back to us.

293
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:32,400
Your father will come back.

294
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,433
He loves me.

295
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:43,000
He loves us so much.

296
00:21:46,967 --> 00:21:48,967
Mother, don't be sad now.

297
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:22,200
Mother...

298
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:25,567
let's go to sleep.

299
00:22:25,633 --> 00:22:26,767
It's already midnight.

300
00:22:31,733 --> 00:22:33,033
Mother, come on.

301
00:22:34,867 --> 00:22:37,100
You've been crying
and not sleeping for weeks.

302
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:38,500
Let's go, Mother.

303
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:41,033
Go to sleep, Mother.

304
00:22:53,467 --> 00:22:55,000
Mother, let's eat now.

305
00:22:58,033 --> 00:22:59,133
Mother...

306
00:23:01,100 --> 00:23:02,533
Mother?

307
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:03,967
Mother?

308
00:23:04,033 --> 00:23:06,000
Mother, wake up.

309
00:23:06,067 --> 00:23:07,867
Mother, let's eat.

310
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:09,700
Mother?

311
00:23:09,767 --> 00:23:10,933
No, no...

312
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,133
Mother, no.

313
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:15,733
Mother, come on, wake up.

314
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,333
Mother, listen to me...

315
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,767
Wake up, Mother.

316
00:23:19,833 --> 00:23:21,300
Mother...

317
00:23:32,133 --> 00:23:34,100
My child, I'm sorry.

318
00:23:34,167 --> 00:23:35,933
It's really an emergency.

319
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,433
I didn't forget that today

320
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:40,800
is your mother Lucinda's death
anniversary.

321
00:23:40,867 --> 00:23:42,967
Honestly, I never remember
a single day,

322
00:23:43,033 --> 00:23:44,967
an important day in my life
that you were there...

323
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:51,400
Birthday, Christmas,
New Year, graduation.

324
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,500
Did I say anything?

325
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:57,700
Did I make a fuss about it?

326
00:23:57,767 --> 00:23:59,000
You didn't hear anything
from me.

327
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:03,600
I was only asking for one day...

328
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:07,000
one day.

329
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:11,500
You know how important
this day to me is.

330
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:14,600
I was only asking for one
day and you can't give it.

331
00:24:17,233 --> 00:24:19,000
Father, you can't give one
day...

332
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:21,700
for me...

333
00:24:21,767 --> 00:24:23,033
for your daughter?

334
00:24:47,133 --> 00:24:47,533
It's your father.

335
00:24:48,767 --> 00:24:49,867
- Patricio...
- Father.

336
00:24:49,933 --> 00:24:51,433
you still haven't seen
Celeste?

337
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:52,467
I'm still looking for her.

338
00:24:53,667 --> 00:24:54,967
Father, you should let her
cool down.

339
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:57,600
I have a bad feeling.

340
00:24:58,833 --> 00:24:59,567
Maybe she will not go home.

341
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:04,367
Father, Celeste is old enough.

342
00:25:04,467 --> 00:25:05,500
She knows what she's doing.

343
00:25:06,633 --> 00:25:09,300
I will not go home
until I find your sister.

344
00:25:10,367 --> 00:25:12,067
If you want to go home,
then go!

345
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:16,900
Sebastian, don't talk anymore.

346
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:21,833
I always hurt Celeste.

347
00:25:23,467 --> 00:25:27,633
I hope this day won't end
without making amends with her.

348
00:25:32,067 --> 00:25:33,933
Patricio, be hopeful.

349
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,200
We will find Celeste.

350
00:26:03,633 --> 00:26:04,600
Hello, Sir?

351
00:26:05,667 --> 00:26:07,233
Mikoy...

352
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:09,100
Mikoy...

353
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:11,200
we need your help.

354
00:26:11,267 --> 00:26:12,900
Celeste is missing.

355
00:26:12,967 --> 00:26:14,100
Let's look for her.

356
00:26:15,467 --> 00:26:16,600
What?

357
00:26:43,967 --> 00:26:44,967
What's with that Basti

358
00:26:45,033 --> 00:26:46,767
and you agreed
with his suggestions?

359
00:26:46,833 --> 00:26:48,300
Are you jealous, Babe?

360
00:26:48,367 --> 00:26:50,000
I know that his intention
is bad.

361
00:26:50,967 --> 00:26:52,000
What are you doing?

362
00:26:52,067 --> 00:26:53,233
Wait.

363
00:26:53,300 --> 00:26:54,733
Just relax.

364
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:55,867
It's gross.

365
00:26:55,933 --> 00:26:58,267
In four months' time,
Celeste and I will get married.

366
00:26:58,333 --> 00:27:01,000
And yet my bride
is in community service.

367
00:27:01,067 --> 00:27:03,867
Is there a way to speed up
her community service?

368
00:27:03,933 --> 00:27:05,600
I already talked to the mayor.

369
00:27:05,667 --> 00:27:06,967
I'm begging you.

370
00:27:07,033 --> 00:27:10,333
Don't come back
without my daughter.

371
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,133
I think you're good to go.

372
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,233
It's already late.

373
00:27:16,433 --> 00:27:18,567
Do you remember the day
when I carved this?

374
00:27:18,633 --> 00:27:21,400
That was also the day
when we kissed.

375
00:27:21,467 --> 00:27:23,400
What?

376
00:27:23,467 --> 00:27:25,600
Celeste's nagging ways
are getting out of hand.

377
00:27:25,667 --> 00:27:27,267
She is narrow-minded.

378
00:27:27,333 --> 00:27:29,900
Let's just be more understanding
to her.

379
00:27:29,967 --> 00:27:30,867
Do you remember me?

380
00:27:30,933 --> 00:27:32,467
I'm Celeste's fiancé.

381
00:27:32,533 --> 00:27:34,200
Yes, Tonito.

382
00:27:34,267 --> 00:27:35,567
And I'm starting to worry

383
00:27:35,633 --> 00:27:37,467
if something bad happened
to her.

384
00:27:37,533 --> 00:27:40,233
Tonito, something bad
happened to her.

385
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:41,767
What?
